-- Vatican Bank to Publish Balance Sheet for First Time, Ansa Says
-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2013-05-14T15:27:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-14/vatican-bank-to-publish-balance-sheet-for-first-time-ansa-says.html
The Vatican bank will publish its
financial accounts for the first time by the end of 2013,
Italian news agency Ansa reported, citing remarks made by the
bank’s head, Ernst von Freyberg.  The Vatican bank, which is formally called the Institute
for the Works of Religion, or IOR, will also have its balance
sheet audited, Ansa cited Von Freyberg as telling the bank’s
employees at a meeting today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lorenzo Totaro in Rome at 
 ltotaro@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
